&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7. Intel Compute Stick:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
For an ultra-compact option, consider the Intel Compute Stick. It&amp;#8217;s a small device that plugs directly into an HDMI port and turns any compatible display into a mini PC. While less powerful than some other options, it&amp;#8217;s highly portable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;imageblock&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;images/imgx0002700108.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;imgx0002700108&quot;&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;paragraph&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;8. Acer Chromebox:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
If you&amp;#8217;re interested in a mini PC for web browsing, document editing, and lightweight tasks, the Acer Chromebox is a cost-effective option. It runs Chrome OS and is powered by Intel processors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;imageblock&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;content&quot;&gt;
&lt;img src=&quot;images/imgx0002700109.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;imgx0002700109&quot;&gt;
